==================== 2.27.2 ====================

==================== 2.27.1 ====================

==================== 2.22.2 ====================

==================== 2.22.1 ====================

2008-03-09  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.22.0

2008-02-26  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* privileges-table.c (privilege_search): Check that the group name is
	not NULL. Fixes #518785.

2008-02-25  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.21.92

2008-02-18  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* callbacks.c (on_table_button_press): Check that we're receiving the
	event on treeview's bin_window.

2008-02-12  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.21.91

2008-01-28  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.21.90

2008-01-16  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* callbacks.c (on_user_settings_clicked): plug a potential leak.

2008-01-15  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.21.5.1

2008-01-15  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.21.5

2008-01-07  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* user-settings.c (user_settings_dialog_new) (check_login)
	(check_comments) (check_home) (check_uid) (check_shell)
	(check_password) (user_settings_dialog_run)
	(user_settings_dialog_get_data): avoid having to call
	user_settings_dialog_get_data() too early, creating a NULL OobsUser in
	consequence.

2008-01-02  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* user-settings.c (check_home): Check whether the home directory
	doesn't exist, Fixes #300016.

2008-01-02  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* user-settings.c (user_settings_dialog_new): Do not set anything in
	the password fields when editing an user, so it doesn't mislead users
	believing that it contains the actual user password. Fixes #169574.
	(check_password): Only check it if it has changed.

2008-01-02  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* callbacks.c (on_user_new_clicked): Do not create an user with NULL
	login name here.
	(on_user_settings_login_changed): Do not check whether the user is
	new, old users can't change login name anymore.
	* user-settings.[ch] (user_settings_dialog_get_data): Instead create
	the user here if we're creating a new user. Fixes #505115.
	(set_main_group) (user_settings_dialog_new) (is_user_root)
	(check_login) (user_settings_dialog_run): Adapt to the possibility of
	having a NULL user.
	(user_settings_dialog_is_new): Remove, no longer used.

2007-12-26  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* users-tool.c: Use HIG compliant capitalization for window title.
	Fixes #474645.

2007-12-18  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.21.3

2007-12-12  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	Use editing mode, which will ask whether to update the configuration
	if a modifiation is in course and the underlying configuration changes
	(file monitoring was added in s-t-b 2.5.4). Everything together fixes
	#488859.

	* group-settings.c (check_group_delete) (group_settings_dialog_run):
	* user-settings.c (check_user_delete) (user_settings_dialog_run): Turn
	editing mode on when the dialogs are running.

	* groups-table.[ch] (groups_table_clear): Added.
	* privileges-table.[ch] (privileges_table_clear): Added.
	* users-table.[ch] (users_table_clear): Added.
	* users-tool.c (update_users) (update_groups): Use these here.

2007-11-14  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.21.2.1

2007-11-14  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* callbacks.c: cover all PolicyKit usage under HAVE_POLKIT.

2007-11-13  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.21.2

2007-11-13  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* user-settings.c (user_settings_dialog_new)
	(user_settings_dialog_get_data): disallow changing login name.
	* group-settings.c (group_settings_dialog_new)
	(group_settings_dialog_get_data): ditto for group name.

2007-11-12  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* privileges-table.c: use a GtkTreeModelFilter so groups with no
	description are not shown, but taken into account anyway.

2007-11-12  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* user-settings.c (set_main_group): make sure that the combobox
	selection is resetted if the user has no main group.

2007-11-12  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* callbacks.c (on_user_settings_clicked): use OobsSelfConfig if the
	tool is not authenticated and the edited user is the requester one.
	* users-tool.[ch]: add OobsSelfConfig.

2007-10-30  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

        * Release 2.21.1

2007-10-18  Denis Washington  <denisw@svn.mate.org>

	* callbacks.[ch]:
	* main.c:
	* users-table.c:
	* users-tool.c: Allow an unauthenticated user to change some of his
	own properties, e.g. the password. All other users are shown insensitive
	and cannot be edited (frontend-wise; restrictions in s-t-b will follow).

2007-10-15  Denis Washington  <denisw@svn.mate.org>

	* main.c: Use gst_dialog_require_authentication_for_widgets() to
	mark those widgets which need authentication to be used.

2007-09-29  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* users-tool.c: Adapt to liboobs 2.21.x API change.

2007-09-13  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* table.c (setup_shells_combo): setup text column properly, it was
	relying on libglade before.

2007-09-13  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* user-settings.c (check_user_delete): check whether the user is
	active and show a warning if he/she is in the delete dialog.

2007-09-06  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* users-tool.c (gst_users_tool_constructor): Added, get mateconf values
	there, after tool->name has been set. Fixes #466183
	(on_showall_changed): actually get the MateConfValue.

2007-09-03  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.19.92

2007-08-28  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.19.91

2007-07-28  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.19.1

2007-07-10  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.19.0

2007-06-18  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* privileges-table.c: constify privilege descriptions array
	(privilege_search): use correct key for bsearch(), fix a compiler
	warning.

2007-04-09  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.18.1

2007-04-08  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* group-members-table.c (user_name_cell_data_func): Added, cell data
	func to ensure that at least the login name will be shown if there's
	no full name. Fixes #425020.

2007-03-12  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.18.0

2007-02-27  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.17.92

2007-02-12  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.17.91

2007-02-11  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* callbacks.c: mark a few dialogs as transient for another ones. Fixes
	#392720.

2007-01-09  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.17.5

2007-01-08  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.17.4

2006-12-01  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.17.3

2006-11-30  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* main.c:
	* callbacks.c (on_manage_groups_clicked) (on_groups_dialog_show_help):
	show help correctly in the groups dialog. Fixes bug #378425.

2006-11-15  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* user-settings.c (check_user_delete) (check_password): string
	improvements (hopefully!)

2006-11-14  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* user-settings.c (check_password): patch by Sebastien Bacher 
	<seb128@debian.org> to allow random passwords. Fixes #355432.

2006-11-10  Kjartan Maraas  <kmaraas@mate.org>

	* callbacks.c: (on_user_settings_profile_changed):
	* main.c:
	* privileges-table.c: (find_group_in_profile):
	* user-profiles.c: (gst_user_profiles_init):
	* user-settings.c: (set_main_group):
	Fix compiler warnings.

2006-11-05  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.17.2

2006-11-04  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* callbacks.c, group-settings.c, groups-table.c, user-settings.c,
	users-table.c: better memory management for OobsUser, OobsGroup and
	OobsListIter objects inside tree models. plug some leaks on the way.

2006-09-30  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.15.5

2006-09-07  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.15.4

2006-09-04  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.15.3

2006-08-28  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	Add back profiles support to users-admin, now the profiles will be a
	read-only key file located in /etc/mate-system-tools/users/profiles,
	distros are supposed to implement that file according to their
	requirements, I doubt that users ever created a profile, so that's no
	longer supported.

	* user-profiles.[ch]: added, object to manage user profiles
	* Makefile.am: add these files.
	* callbacks.[ch] (on_user_settings_login_changed): add a way to 
	override the default homedir prefix.
	(on_user_settings_profile_changed): added, applies a profile when the
	profiles combo changes.
	* main.c: connect that callback to the profiles combo
	* privileges-table.c (find_group_in_profile)
	(privileges_table_set_from_profile): new functions, set the
	privileges table state from a profile
	* table.[ch] (table_populate_profiles) (table_set_default_profile): 
	Added.
	* user-settings.[ch] (find_new_uid): pass max_uid and min_uid as
	parameters.
	(setup_profiles_visibility): Added.
	(user_settings_dialog_new): Setup GUI initially according to the 
	profile.
	(user_settings_apply_profile): added, changes the UI given a profile.
	* users-tool.[ch]: add profiles object.

2006-08-23  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* users-tool.c (gst_users_tool_update_config): added.

2006-08-11  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.15.2

2006-08-02  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.15.1

2006-06-06  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.15.0

2006-06-05  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* md5.[ch], md5_crypt.c: deleted. Functionality moved to Liboobs
	* profile-settings.[ch]: deleted
	* profiles-table.[ch]: ditto
	* user-group-xml.[ch]: ditto
	* user_group.[ch]: ditto

2006-06-05  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* callbacks.c (on_user_new_clicked) (on_user_settings_clicked): commit
	the groups too

2006-05-29  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* group-settings.c, privileges-table.c, user-settings.c: apply some
	string improvement suggestions. Closes #340689

2006-05-27  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

        * table.c: set translation domain for action_groups. Closes #342497
	(patch by Sebastien Bacher)

2006-05-27  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* users-tool.c: set an icon name
	* users.desktop.in.in: ditto, patch by Sebastien Bacher
	<seb128@debian.org>

2006-05-26  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* group-settings.[ch] (group_settings_find_new_gid): export this
	function
	* user-settings.c: use default group for new users, if necessary,
	create a new one

2006-05-22  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* privileges-table.c: remove an unnecessary cast

2006-05-19  Carlos Garnacho  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* users-tool.[ch]: new GObject, inherits from GstTool, and provides
	access to the necessary OobsObjects.
	* group-members-table.[ch]: added. It's table to show users/group
	members.
	* test-battery.[ch]: added. Provides functions to run series of tests
	over something (say an user or a group), replaces the former 
	if/else if/else if/else if/... mess.
	* transfer.[ch]: to the Attic, XML interface is deprecated.
	* Makefile.am: reflect those changes. Do not compile the search bar.
	* callbacks.[ch], group-settings.[ch], user-settings.[ch]: adapt to
	liboobs. remove/comment out unused code.
	* groups-table.[ch], users-table.[ch]: store pointers to user/group
	objects.
	* main.c, passwd.[ch]: code cleanup
	* privileges-table.c: store the mapping table of groups -> privilege
	here, no longer use the <allows_to> hack
	* table.[ch]: cleanup and code improvements. Use the same model in
	several places, filtering where necessary.

2006-03-13  Carlos Garnacho Parro  <carlosg@mate.org>

	* Release 2.14.0

